==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Engouled
<hw>En*gouled"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Her.)</fld>
<def>Partly swallowed; disappearing in the jaws of anything; <as>as, an
infant <ex>engouled</ex> by a serpent</as>; said also of an ordinary,
when its two ends to issue from the mouths of lions, or the like;
<as>as, a bend <ex>engouled</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Engoulee</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
